[metadata]
Name:Ironclaw Orcs can't block power 2 or greater
Goal:Survive
Turns:3
Difficulty:Easy
Description:mtg-512. Ironclaw Orcs (2/2) carries S:Mode$ CantBlockBy | ValidAttacker$ Creature.powerGE2 | ValidBlocker$ Creature.Self ("can't block creatures with power 2 or greater", CR 509.1b / 509.4). P2 attacks each turn with Hill Giant (3/3). The Orcs must NOT be a legal blocker for it, so Hill Giant's 3 damage hits P1 every combat even though an untapped 2/2 is sitting on P1's battlefield. Before the fix the restriction was silently dropped and the Orcs could illegally block (and trade with) the Giant.

# Regression for mtg-512: the Mode$ CantBlockBy | ValidBlocker$ Creature.Self
# block-restriction (Ironclaw Orcs) lowers to StaticAbility::CantBlockMatching
# and is enforced in combat_rules::can_block. The per-pair predicate is also
# unit-tested in tests/blocker_legality_test.rs
# (ironclaw_orcs_cant_block_power_2_or_greater).
[state]
turn=4
activeplayer=p1
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0battlefield=Ironclaw Orcs
p0library=Mountain; Mountain; Mountain
p1life=20
p1hand=
p1battlefield=Hill Giant
p1library=Forest; Forest; Forest
